    "Results on the ATIS dataset can be found in table 3.While the choice of the class name is inconsequential for an encoder-only model, it significantly influences decoder-only models.",
    "As an example, we fine-tuned three versions of LLaMA2 on the Banking dataset: the first one in which the intents had the original names, the second one in which the intent names were removed of underscores and replaced with white spaces, and the last one in which the prefix Sentiment AnalysisA fine-tuned LLaMA2 outperforms a fine-tuned RoBERTa on the sentiment analysis task, but not by a large margin, as seen in table 5.",
    "Positive and Negative classes are universal.",
    "It is observed that LLaMA2 struggles with zero and few-shot inference on datasets having more classes than the traditional positive and negative ones.",
    "The Tweet-Eval dataset contains negative, neutral and positive as classes, and the model performs poorly for the neutral class."
